$ kernel/reboot.c

This file defines the entry point for the following → Linux/kernel/sys-calls[syscalls]: `reboot`.

{ ctrl_alt_del()

  The function `ctrl_alt_del()` is ccalled when ctrl+alt+del (the keyboard interrupt) is pressed.

}

sa:

  `sbin/ctrlaltdel` (part of → Linux/utilities#util-linux).
